<section id="slide-orga05d6f1">
<h4 id="orga05d6f1">Denoising a signals</h4>
<ul>
<li>The approximate coeffiient contain the low frequency contents so we can think it has filtered signal</li>

</ul>

<div class="figure">
<p><img src="./denoising signals.png" alt="denoising signals.png" />
</p>
</div>
</section>
</section>
<section>
<section id="slide-orge441970">
<h2 id="orge441970">Uses of wavelet transform</h2>
<ul>
<li>Used in image compression (jpeg 2000)</li>
<li>image denoising</li>
<li>Edge detaction</li>
<li>image enhancement</li>
<li>image fusion</li>

</ul>
</section>
</section>
<section>
<section id="slide-org1fb3db4">
<h2 id="org1fb3db4">How to denoise signal using wavelets</h2>
<ul>
<li>To denoise a signals all detailed coeffients are passed to and shrinked</li>
<li>some of the coeffients are cut off by threshold</li>
<li>there is somany methi=od for thresholding like minimax method</li>
<li>The detailed coeffients are considers as noise that why processing is only done to it only</li>

</ul>
</section>
